	<h1>Troubleshooting</h1>
	<p class="tagline">Common issues and how to fix them.</p>

	<h2 id="notes-not-showing">Notes Not Showing</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Check your filters and paths.</p>

	<p>Verify the correct symbol is selected in Symbol Manager. Check that "All Tags" is selected if you're not filtering by tag. Confirm the note status matches where you're looking - an Active note won't appear in Archives.</p>

	<p>If notes still don't appear, open Settings and verify the Notes Root Folder path points to the correct directory.</p>

	<h2 id="trade-data-not-loading">Trade Data Not Loading</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Verify database configuration.</p>

	<p>Open Settings and check that the Trade Database path points to your trades.json file. Ensure the file is a valid MT5 export format and that ThinkPad has read permissions for the file location.</p>

	<h2 id="incorrect-trade-times">Incorrect Trade Times</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Adjust your timezone offset.</p>

	<p>Open Settings and go to the Trade tab. Set the UTC offset to match your local timezone, then save. All trade times now display in your local time.</p>
</DocsLayout>
